  My primary focus is to understand : 

    - Why SIEM exists ? 
      *To solve the impossible tasks of manually monitoring massive scattered IT envieronments. It acts as an organization seccurity "nervous system" by collecting . aggregating and correlating logs in real-time to spot hidden
       attacks , speed up incident response and simplify compliance audits.Gartner defines SIEM as a configurable system of record that collects, aggregates and analyzes security event data from on-premises and cloud environments.

    - Why Splunk was selected over traditional command-line tools?
      *WIth its massive achievements of being named a Leader 11 times in a row , Thousands of organizations worldwide rely on Splunk Enterprise Security as their SIEM to rapidly detect and respond to critical events so they cna stay ahead
       of emerging threats and maintain cyber resilience. With the ability to perform a wide range of security analytics and operations use cases, organizations can remain flexible and agile in the face of evolving threats and business needs.

       source of information for the above questions : (https://www.splunk.com/en_us/form/gartner-siem-magic-quadrant.html?utm_campaign=google_emea_tier1_en_search_generic_security_siem&utm_source=google&utm_medium=cpc&utm_content=GartnerMQ25_AR&utm_term=siem%20security&device=c&_bt=779298826963&_bm=p&_bn=g&gad_source=1&gad_campaignid=8200497833&gbraid=0AAAAAD8kDz2q2SY4u3GmYRJX6lJu7o0JY&gclid=Cj0KCQjw3qLSBhDaARIsAFTiVh6sOd69L44uRyQlCs0-_q1TKdSOs3fZ7OjBfoG6aYnpV6KnwJCDBBoaAj1-EALw_wcB)


    - Why APIs have become a major security target?
      * By nature, APIs expose application logic and sensitive data such as Personally Identifiable Information (PII) and because of this have increasingly become a target for attackers. Without secure APIs, rapid innovation would be impossible.
        Source: (https://owasp.org/www-project-api-security/)
    
    - Why crAPI is more suitable than OWASP Juice Shop for this research?
      crAPI (Completely Ridiculous API) is more suitable than OWASP Juice Shop because the goal is specifically to learn, test, or train for modern API security. While Juice Shop covers traditional web app flaws (like XSS and SQLi), 
      crAPI focuses directly on the OWASP API Security Top 10 since this project is to mainly focus on the OWASP atacks in specific.
      
      
      
